	 <h1 class="storytitle">2016</h1>

	<p> Dominic Galliano, <a href="http://www.iopblog.org/is-it-ok-to-be-gay-what-we-learned-from-the-aps-lgbt-in-physics-report/">We still have a long way to go: what we learned from the APS LGBT+ in physics report</a>, <b>Institute of Physics Blog</b>, March 23, 2016.</p>
	 
	<p> Elizabeth Gibney, <a href="http://www.scientificamerican.com/article/lgbt-physicists-face-discrimination-exclusion-intimidation/">LGBT Physicists Face Discrimination, Exclusion, Intimidation</a>, <b>Scientific American</b>, March 22, 2016.</p>

	<p> Elizabeth Gibney, <a href="http://www.nature.com/news/excluded-intimidated-and-harassed-lgbt-physicists-face-discrimination-1.19614">Excluded, intimidated and harassed: LGBT physicists face discrimination</a>, <b>Nature</b>, March 22, 2016.</p>

	 <p> Andrew Ellson, <a href="http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/science/article4717855.ece">Gay bigotry collides with particle physics</a>, <b>The Times</b>, March 21, 2016.</p>

	 <p> Colleen Flaherty, <a href="https://www.insidehighered.com/news/2016/03/16/new-effort-improve-climate-lgbt-physicists">Climate Concerns Among LGBT Physicists</a>, <b>Inside Higher Ed</b>, March 16, 2016.</p>

	 <p> Jos Truitt, <a href="http://feministing.com/2016/03/16/new-report-shows-need-to-improve-working-conditions-for-lgbt-physicists/">New Report Shows Need to Improve Working Conditions for LGBT Physicists</a>, <b>Feministing</b>, March 16, 2016.</p>

	 <p> Matin Durrani, <a href="http://blog.physicsworld.com/2016/03/15/aps-launches-lgbt-climate-in-physics-report/">APS launches 'LGBT Climate in Physics' report</a>, <b>Physics World Blog</b>, March 15, 2016.</p>

	 <p> Michael Falk, Elena Long <a href="http://www.aps.org/publications/apsnews/201603/backpage.cfm">Is Physics Open and Accepting for LGBT People?</a>, <b>APS News</b>, March, 2016.</p>

	 <p> Savannah Garmon, Elizabeth Simmons <a href="https://www.aps.org/programs/women/reports/gazette/upload/spr16.pdf">The APS Committee on LGBT Issues: Findings and Recommendations</a>, <b>CSWP &amp; COM Gazette</b>, Spring, 2016.</p>

	<hr>

	 <h1 class="storytitle">2015</h1>

	 <p> Jeremy B. Yoder and Allison Mattheis, <a href="http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/00918369.2015.1078632#.VcjRTnUVhBc">Queer in STEM: Workplace Experiences Reported in a National Survey of LGBTQA Individuals in Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics Careers</a>, <b>Journal of Homosexuality</b>, August 4, 2015.</p>

	 <p> Elena Long, <a href="http://blog.physicsworld.com/2015/07/31/the-august-2015-issue-of-physics-world-is-now-out/">Removing Barriers</a>, <b>Physics World</b>, August, 2015.</p>

	 <p> Toni Feder, <a href="http://scitation.aip.org/content/aip/magazine/physicstoday/article/68/3/10.1063/PT.3.2716">APS looks to improve climate for LGBT physicists</a>, <b>Physics Today</b>, March, 2015.</p>
 

	 <p> Toni Feder, <a href="http://scitation.aip.org/content/aip/magazine/physicstoday/news/10.1063/PT.5.9034">LGBT physicists: The interviews</a>, <b>Physics Today: Singularities</b>, February, 2015.</p>
	
	<hr>

	 <h1 class="storytitle">2014</h1>
	 <p> Elena Long, <a href="http://www.spsobserver.org/2014/fall.pdf">Navigating Physics as a Fish out of Water</a>, <b>SPS Observer</b>, Pages 20-21, Fall 2014.</p> 

	 <p> Wouter Deconinck, <a href="./files/media/2014_SEAPS_Wouter.pdf">Improving the Climate for LGBT+ Physicists</a>, <b>South Eastern APS Section Meeting</b>, November 13, 2014.</p> 

	 <p> Michael Lucibella, <a href="http://www.aps.org/publications/apsnews/201411/upload/November-2014.pdf">APS to Study Sexual and Gender Diversity Issues in Physics</a>, <b>APS News</b>, Page 4, November 2014.</p> 

	 <p> Arlene Modeste Knowles, <a href="http://www.aps.org/programs/women/reports/gazette/upload/fall14.pdf">APS Forms Ad Hoc Committee on Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual, Transgender Issues</a>, <b>CSWP & COM Gazette</b>, Page 10, Fall 2014.</p> 

	 <p> Adam Smith, <a href="http://www.researchresearch.com/index.php?option=com_news&template=rr_2col&view=article&articleId=1343792">LGBT academics aim to wipe out 'don't ask, don't tell' culture</a>, <b>ResearchResearch</b>, May 14, 2014.</p> 
	  	      
	 <p> Cameron Walker, <a href="http://www.nature.com/naturejobs/science/articles/10.1038/nj7482-249a">Equality: Standing out</a>, <b>Nature Jobs</b>, January 8, 2014.</p> 
	  	      
