	 <h1 class="storytitle">2013</h1>

	 <p> Jeremy Yoder, <a href="http://www.queerstem.org/2013/07/helping-to-change-climate-in-academic.html">Helping to change the climate in academic science</a>, <b>Queer in STEM</b>, July 8, 2013.</p> 


	 <p>Elizabeth H. Simmons and Ram&oacute;n S. Barthelemy, <a href="http://www.insidehighered.com/advice/2013/06/21/making-academic-departments-welcoming-lgbt-staff-and-students-essay">Climate Change</a>, <b>Inside Higher Ed</b>, June 21, 2013.</p> 

	 <p>Calla Cofield, <a href="http://www.aps.org/publications/apsnews/201305/upload/May-2013.pdf">A Year of Progress for LGBT+ in Physics</a>, <b>APS News</b>, Page 3, May 2013.</p> 

	<hr>
	 <h1 class="storytitle">2012</h1>
	 <p>Savannah Garmon, <a href="http://www.prettyqueer.com/2012/12/04/sexual-and-gender-diversity-in-physics/">Sexual and Gender Diversity Issues in Physics</a>, <b>PrettyQueer</b>, December 4, 2012.</p> 

	 <p>Tim Atherton, <a href="./files/media/2012_Out_to_Innovate-Tim_Atherton.pdf">Making Physics More Inclusive for LGBT+ People</a>, <b>Out to Innovate</b>, October 2012.</p> 

	 <p>Lisa Grossman, <a href="http://www.newscientist.com/article/dn22115-why-sally-rides-sexuality-really-matters.html#.Ud2R6xdDsyR">Why Sally Ride's sexuality really matters</a>, <b>New Scientist</b>, July 27, 2012.</p>

	 <p>N. Ackerman, T. Atherton, W. Deconinck, M. Falk, S. Garmon, E. Henry, E. Long, <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1206.4112">Gender and Sexual Diversity Issues in Physics: The Audience Speaks</a>, <b>arXiv:1206.4112</b>, June 19, 2012.</p> 

	 <p>Vijaysree Venkatraman, <a href="http://www.sciencemag.org/careers/2012/06/just-herself">Gravitational wave researcher succeeds by being herself</a>, <b>Science Careers</b>, June 1, 2012.</p> 

	 <p>Wouter Deconinck, <a href="http://www.aapt.org/Conferences/upload/Sexual-and-Gender-Diversity-Deconinck.pdf">Sexual and Gender Diversity
</a>, <i>Developing an Inclusive Diversity Climate</i>, <b>AAPT Physics Department Chairs Conference</b>, June 2012.</p> 


	 <p>Calla Cofield, <a href="http://www.aps.org/publications/apsnews/201204/upload/april2012.pdf">March Meeting Session Highlights LGBT+ Issues for Physicists</a>, <b>APS News</b>, Page 1, April 2012.</p> 

	 <p>Margaret Harris, <a href="http://blog.physicsworld.com/2012/03/01/drawing-noise-and-speaking-out/">Drawing noise and speaking out</a>, <b>physicsworld.com</b>, March 1, 2012.</p> 

	 <p>Eric Patridge and Ram&oacute;n Barthelemy, <a href="http://meetings.aps.org/Meeting/MAR12/Session/J20.1">The State of Higher Education for STEM LGBTQQ Faculty/Staff</a>, <i>Sexual and Gender Diversity Issues in Physics</i>, <b>APS March Meeting</b>, February 28, 2012.</p> 

	 <p>Michael Ramsey-Musolf, <a href="http://meetings.aps.org/Meeting/MAR12/Session/J20.2">Shattering the Lavender Ceiling: Sexual Minorities in Physics</a>, <i>Sexual and Gender Diversity Issues in Physics</i>, <b>APS March Meeting</b>, February 28, 2012.</p> 

	 <p>Janice Hicks, <a href="http://meetings.aps.org/Meeting/MAR12/Session/J20.3">Why Awareness of LGBT issues in the Physics Community Makes Sense</a>, <i>Sexual and Gender Diversity Issues in Physics</i>, <b>APS March Meeting</b>, February 28, 2012.</p> 

	 <p>Elena Long, <a href="http://meetings.aps.org/Meeting/MAR12/Session/J20.4">Physics Climate as Experienced by LGBT+ Physicists</a>, <i>Sexual and Gender Diversity Issues in Physics</i>, <b>APS March Meeting</b>, February 28, 2012.</p> 


